com.i2group.apollo.externaldata.edrs

Interface IExternalDataRetrievalConnector


  • public interface IExternalDataRetrievalConnector
    A pair of methods that an external data retrieval service calls to retrieve Items from an external data source.
    Since:
    4.0

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      ExternalDataContextItemsResults getContext(List<ProvenanceGroup> provenanceGroups, int maxNumberOfItems, boolean shouldThrowIfTooManyItems)
      Gets an ExternalDataContextItemsResults that contains Items from an external data source that are indirectly associated with the CardProvenances in the specified ProvenanceGroups.

      • getContext

        ExternalDataContextItemsResults getContext(List<ProvenanceGroup> provenanceGroups,
                                           int maxNumberOfItems,
                                           boolean shouldThrowIfTooManyItems)
        Gets an ExternalDataContextItemsResults that contains Items from an external data source that are indirectly associated with the CardProvenances in the specified ProvenanceGroups.
        Parameters:
        provenanceGroups - ProvenanceGroups that contain CardProvenances for the Items that are associated with the Items to be retrieved.
        maxNumberOfItems - The maximum number of Items that the ExternalDataContextItemsResults can contain.
        shouldThrowIfTooManyItems - true to throw an exception (and return no results) when the number of Items in ExternalDataContextItemsResults would exceed maxNumberOfItems; false to throw no exception and return up to maxNumberOfItems results. If maxNumberOfItems is not exceeded, this parameter has no effect.
        Returns:
        See above.
